  <p><em>This is a <a class="link" href="https://nownownow.com/about">now page</a>. A snapshot of what I'm focused on right now.</em></p>

  <p>Last updated: February 2026</p>

  <h2>At work</h2>

  <p>I'm SVP at Pleo, leading platform, data, IT, and our AI infrastructure buildout. The current focus is on three things: AI infrastructure — building the foundation for AI-powered product capabilities, alongside internal productivity tooling that's already changing how we work. Cost structure — renegotiating card scheme partnerships and optimising our payment processing stack. And growing leaders — I've got a leadership team of 7 running 100+ professionals, and my job is making sure they have the context, autonomy, and support to make great decisions without me.</p>

  <h2>Writing</h2>

  <p>I'm writing about the things I've learned building and scaling at Pleo — organisational design, payments infrastructure, platform engineering, and leadership. You can find it all on the <a class="link" href="/posts/">blog</a>.</p>

  <h2>Exploring</h2>

  <p>How AI reshapes fintech infrastructure — not the product layer but the boring important stuff: fraud detection, transaction monitoring, reconciliation, compliance automation. European payment convergence — SEPA Instant is now mandatory, PSD3 is taking shape, and A2A payments are gaining real traction. And what "platform engineering" actually means — the industry is coalescing around this term but most implementations miss the point.</p>

  <h2>Outside work</h2>

  <p>Listening to a lot of live music. Being a dad. Trying to read more books and fewer newsletters.</p>
